DJ and producer Ashley Raphala, popularly known as Shimza, is bringing his popular One Man Show to the small screens. The event, which normally takes place twice a year in Tembisa, east of Joburg and Soweto, will be aired on MTV Base Africa as a two-hour lockdown special. The special broadcast will be shot at the Union Buildings near the iconic Nelson Mandela statue and all the money that is raised from the event will be donated to the Covid-19 Solidarity Fund and the Nelson Mandela Foundation. The event will be aired on Youth Day, the 16 of June 2020, from 18:00 to 20:00. SEE POST:   